    {
      "order": 6,
      "title": "Self-Learning Hooks & PostgreSQL State",
      "description": "RuVector's claim to fame is that it learns from how you use it. The hooks subsystem is where that happens: `hooks.rs` is a Q-learning engine over patterns, vector-embedded memories, trajectories, error sequences, and file-sequence prediction; `hooks_postgres.rs` is the pgvector-backed persistence layer; and `hooks_schema.sql` is the actual eight-table schema (`ruvector_hooks_patterns`, `_memories`, `_trajectories`, `_errors`, `_file_sequences`, `_swarm_agents`, `_swarm_edges`, `_stats`) that the install writes when you opt into the Postgres backend.",
      "nodeIds": [
        "file:crates/ruvector-cli/src/cli/hooks.rs",
        "file:crates/ruvector-cli/src/cli/hooks_postgres.rs",
        "table:crates/ruvector-cli/sql/hooks_schema.sql"
      ],
      "languageLesson": "pgvector extends Postgres with a `vector` column type and ANN operators (`<=>` cosine, `<#>` inner product, `<->` L2). It lets the hooks engine store learned memories as embeddings directly in SQL and recall them with the same WHERE-clause language used for regular columns \u2014 no separate vector store required."
    },
    {
      "order": 7,
      "title": "The Embedded MCP Server",
      "description": "The install ships a second binary, `ruvector-mcp-server`, that exposes RuVector as a Model Context Protocol endpoint so Claude and other LLM clients can call it as a tool. `mcp_server.rs` is the binary entry point. The `mcp/` module is the implementation: `protocol.rs` defines JSON-RPC and MCP wire types; `handlers.rs` dispatches initialize / tools/list / tools/call and the underlying create_db / insert / search tool handlers; `transport.rs` provides both stdio and an axum-based SSE/HTTP server; `gnn_cache.rs` is an LRU cache of GNN forward passes that keeps tool calls fast.",
