      "languageLesson": "MCP rides on JSON-RPC 2.0: every request is a `{jsonrpc, id, method, params}` envelope, every response carries either a `result` or an `error`. Servers advertise capabilities in `initialize`, then expose tools via `tools/list` and execute them via `tools/call` \u2014 the same handler can be reached over stdio (for spawned subprocesses) or over SSE/HTTP (for networked clients)."
